.TH JSH 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jsh \- Jamie's Shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jsh
is a minimal interactive shell supporting command execution, pipes, and
advanced command chaining[cite: 1]. It uses GNU readline for line editing and history[cite: 2].
.PP
The shell supports the following operators:
.TP
.B |
Pipes the output of one command to the input of the next[cite: 1].
.TP
.B &&
Logical AND; executes the second command only if the first succeeds.
.TP
.B &
Executes the command in the background.
.PP
The shell is quote-aware and will ignore operators inside double quotes (e.g., "&&" or "|").
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B cd [directory]
Change the current working directory[cite: 2].
.TP
.B clear
Clear the terminal screen.
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell[cite: 3].
.TP
.B help
Display a help message with available commands.
.TP
.B history
Display the command history.
.TP
.B ver
Display the current version of JSH.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR readline (3)
